# rockie/.env.example — committed template
#
# Copy to ".env" and fill in real values. The .env file is gitignored
# (see .gitignore and install-assets/gitignore.rockie) so your keys
# never touch git. If you edit install.sh or schema to add new env
# vars, document them here too.
#
# To load these vars in your shell (POSIX-compatible):
#   set -a; . .env; set +a
# Any script rockie runs in that shell session inherits them.

# ─── GPU provisioning mode ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# router  — rockie's GPU router (default; uses GPU_API_KEY below). Set this
#           for autonomous provisioning. The router talks to the deidentified
#           rockie-gpu broker; the underlying compute supplier is selected
#           server-side and never surfaced here.
# custom  — bring your own GPU setup (own AWS account, on-prem cluster, SSH
#           tunnel to a workstation, university quota, etc.). The router is
#           bypassed; the agent runs the /gpu-custom-setup skill on first
#           GPU need and saves your flow to .codex/gpu-custom.md.
# none    — no GPU layer at all (running rockie for non-GPU research).
ROCKIE_GPU_MODE=router

# ─── GPU compute credential (router mode only) ───────────────────────────
# `scripts/gpu.py` is the GPU router. It provisions through the rockie-gpu
# broker using the single credential below; the broker picks the supplier
# and handles preemption-hop and capacity fallback server-side.
GPU_API_KEY=

# Optional: env var holding a pre-registered SSH key id, if your router
# deployment requires one (see `gpu.py --ssh-key-id-env`).
# GPU_SSH_KEY_ID=

# ─── ntfy push notifications (scripts/notify.sh) ─────────────────────────
# Generate a non-guessable topic: `openssl rand -hex 16`
# See docs/ntfy-setup.md for phone-side setup.
NTFY_TOPIC=
# NTFY_SERVER=https://ntfy.sh   # optional; default is public ntfy.sh

# ─── Model-provider keys (if you use alternate LLMs in /deploy-team) ─────
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=        # only if running outside Claude Code
